  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: \"Fetch more messages\" for yesterday's date in chat is disabled after user logs out and logs in again\r\n![Screenshot_20190829-164829_Status](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/63951054-5fe3d400-ca7d-11e9-99b9-665d0948b116.jpg)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\"Fetch more messages\" is enabled and retrieves chat history for the date shown\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n\"Fetch more messages\" is disabled\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=1-jamvAIu7m0Lg2bNekm3T0akkUrSDofd\r\n- Install Status\r\n- Create new account\r\n- Join #status-core public chat or any other chat that has history from yesterday\r\n- check that Fetch more messages option on the top of the chat is enabled\r\n- Use Sign out in Profile to log out\r\n- Enter password and sign in again\r\n- open again same pubic chat and check if  Fetch more messages  is enabled or not\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n- Status version: nightly August 29  https://ci.status.im/job/status-react/job/nightly/1230/\r\n- Operating System: found on Android 9, real Galaxy S10\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[Status-debug-logs (18).zip](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3556150/Status-debug-logs.18.zip)\r\n",
